AGI - At 20.30 the nightmare of their parents is over. The Carabinieri of San Pietro station in Patierno del Nucleo Investigativo di Napoli, in close coordination with staff of the Investment Nucleo of Ravenna, traced the 12-year-old Michelle Carlucci and 13-year-old friend Sofia Rivera Alvares, both of the province of Ravenna, who had disappeared on the morning of 27 March.
&nbsp;
Instead of entering school, the girls were gone without giving news to their parents. The two were located in a building in Corso Arnaldo Lucci where there is also a B&amp;B completely foreign to the story. The children, in a good state of health, will be entrusted to the parents, who are directed to the Carabinieri station of the district of the Campania capital of San Pietro in Parierno.
